22/01/2003
BERLIN, Germany -- Croatian Prime Minister Ivica Racan said during a visit to Germany late Monday (20 January) that his government would file an official application to join the EU either on 18 February in Athens, or on 25 February in Brussels.
Racan is touring European capitals to boost support for his country's bid.
Other stops include Rome, Madrid, London, Dublin, Vienna, Athens and Brussels.
(Vjesnik, HINA, HRT - 21/01/03)
